		<!-- message -->
		<div>Chapter 2: Big Trees, Big Problems <br />
<br />
<br />
The rain continued to pour down from the heavens. Nasu and Relik trotted between the shadows attempting to keep themselves dry. The streets of Qeynos were quiet with the evening that had engulfed the city. Only a handful of lights pierced through the raindrops, flickering out as quickly as they came into vision. The rain falling so serenely on the rooftops and streets of the city reminded Relik of a fresh evenings snow upon Halas. <br />
<br />
&quot;Around here Warrior, we must make haste. The city guards should be searching for us now. We will find peace in Surefall.&quot; Nasu peered over her shoulder at the Barbarian studying his face for a moment. She turned her head back with a flick and continued sprinting across the cobblestone path. <br />
<br />
Relik nodded and proceeded to follow her around a building and through a guard post towards Northern Qeynos. &quot;I'm eager to see Surefall Glade,&quot; Relik thought to himself &quot;I've heard about the rushing waterfall and the huge jagged pine trees. It sounded so peaceful, not at all like a place to plan war. <br />
<br />
The rain tapered off as they ran through the rugged hills north of Qeynos. Nasu motioned for Relik to stop behind some boulders as the moon peaked out from among the scattering clouds. <br />
<br />
&quot;We must proceed with caution. Evil necromancers along with their foul undead servants have long been trying to gain a foothold in these hills. They grow increasingly bold. The tunnel to Surefall Glade is just ahead. I wish to be certain our arrival is unnoticed. We have not been followed from Qeynos luckily. Wait here while I scout around the tunnel.&quot; <br />
<br />
Relik did not like the idea of Nasu going off without him, but then realized she was just as capable of defending herself as he was, if not even more so. He recalled her swift and sure reactions at the inn with an increasing respect and admiration. &quot;She has been well-trained,&quot; he mused, “She will be a valuable ally in any battle and a formidable foe to any who come against us.&quot; His thoughts were cut short when, in a heartbeat she was back, pressing herself flat against the rocks. <br />
<br />
&quot;There is trouble ahead. As I was scouting around the tunnel entrance I came across a few of the Qeynos Guards. They seem to be looking for us.&quot; Nasu panted. <br />
<br />
&quot;So what should we do?&quot; said Relik as he unsheathed his swords. <br />
&quot;Nothing like what you're thinking warrior.&quot; Nasu raised her eyebrow at the steel that Relik displayed. &quot;This can be relatively easy if we move swiftly and quietly. There is no need to shed innocent blood, they aren't the ones out to kill us.&quot; <br />
<br />
Relik nodded as he shoved his swords back in their sheathes. He was glad that he didn't have to kill anymore that day. Even though he was good at his trade he never really enjoyed killing. &quot;I'm in trouble if I ever start to enjoy what I do.&quot; Relik thought to himself. <br />
<br />
Nasu had pulled out her spell book and began to look across the pages in a hurry. After a few seconds of searching she finally came across the page that she was looking for. She began to recite over and over again the words that were in the book for a few seconds and then looked up at Relik. The warrior’s eyes began to tingle a little but other than that he didn't notice any change in anything. After saying it once more Nasu looked up at Relik. <br />
&quot;Now, I'm going to be able to camouflage us so no one will be able to see us go through the tunnel. The spell doesn’t last long and if you make any noises or any sudden movements it will wear off. You will become visible again.&quot; <br />
<br />
Relik nodded once more. &quot;I'm ready ranger, give me your best.&quot; <br />
<br />
The ranger began to recite a few words and in a brief flash the world went gray. Everything was black and white and the only things that appeared natural were Nasu and Himself. Motioning for him to follow her Nasu leaped swiftly yet quietly from behind the rock and moved towards the entrance to Surefall. <br />
<br />
&quot;...warrior and an elven ranger, you sure you haven’t seen em?&quot; said a guard as Nasu and Relik quietly snuck around their pursuers. Relik noticed that he was holding his breath and that he was worried to make any noise. The ranger quietly tugged on his arm leading him through the entrance. The tunnel wasn't too long and before he knew it he was inside the town, and everything turned into their normal colors again. <br />
<br />
&quot;LEAVE THE DAMN BEARS OF SUREFALL GLADE ALONE!&quot; Shouted a voice that echoed through the woods and reverberated off the trees.</div>
